Happy Birthday Robby!
My present to you is sharing this amazing video from 2014!
🎁🎂🎉🥳💩
So here’s the “back story”…
We were mountain biking and @rdgmoonville had already had an emergency in an area of the State Park where he could walk off the trail and into the woods to poop in privacy.  He walked back telling @motojunkie and me that he sure hoped the @chickfila salad didn’t kick in again. 
Well, 5 mins later when we’re half way up a long climb where the trail’s super narrow with a near vertical wall on one side and a deep ravine on the other… it hit him! 😳
Lucky for Robby, it hit when he was beside this tree that he thought offered a bit of privacy. Being the friends that we are, I immediately began recording the predicament while Harvey pretended there were some ladies hiking thru the narrow pass saying “Come on thru M’am”. 
🤣
After pooping all over his bibs, Harvey was a true friend and helped with the camelback. I would’ve helped but I was busy filming and even said “A true friend is this video and not showing it to anybody”. 🤳🏻
Somehow, with new phones and time, I’d lost this video for over 5yrs until it mysteriously showed up in my iCloud files. The lesson is, choose your friends wisely and be careful what you have on your iCloud.
I’m thankful to have this hilarious memory and I’m forever grateful for Robby & Harvey’s friendships and the countless good times we’ve shared! 🙏

Happy (belated) Mother’s Day 💐
All Mom wanted was for my sister and me to go to Church with her and Dad, then a relaxing afternoon together. I’m so thankful for the Godly example my parents have always been to Cindy, me, and our entire family. 
Mom still has a Proverbs 22:6 framed in our childhood bathroom at her house. It says; “Train up a child in the way he should go and when he is old he will not depart from it” 🚂
Well, my train has certainly gone off the tracks a number of times in my life but my Mom was always there with unwavering and unconditional love. Thank You Mom for ALL that you mean to our family. ❤️🙏🙌

#FBF to 1995 ripping the “tree turn” on my private SX track behind my Dad’s machine shop while defending the title Fastest Man In Piedmont!
🏆
Through the early 90’s, and LONG before facilities existed, that track SX hosted top level Pros the likes of @browniemx @jsr_111 @nramsey25 @jimneese @jchester8 @dehaan104 @guaranteedmx @charleybogard Jeromy Buehl, Todd Dehoop, Greg Rand, James Eickel just to make a few. 
The second pic is what the “tree turn” looks like today. Dad sold his business and the property beside my parents home years ago but I still have fond memories of that place on earth.
🌳
Things I miss 28yrs later…
- That track
- That dirt
- That 1995 CR250
- That box van
😢
Things I still have 28yrs later…
- That helmet
- Those goggles
- That jersey 
- Those pants 
- THAT TITLE! 
☝🏻👨🏻 
(Special thanks to @motomatters186 for the 📸)

#FatFaceFriday 👀
My buddy @rdgmoonville sent me these pics from a 2005 @twmxdotcom issue he still has. 

Had one of the interview questions been; 
How many Cokes do you drink each day at the races? 

My answer would’ve been;
“About 8 to 10” 🤦🏻‍♂️

I’d also drink several sitting in First Class on the Delta flights, often times with @rickycarmichael looking on in envy as @aldon104 wouldn’t let him have soft drinks. Aldon would tell me they were horrible for me, but I just kept drinking them. 

I’m thankful for that one kidney stone later that year and the excruciating pain that immediately broke me of the habit as I’m much leaner and healthier today than I was 18yrs ago. 

*And no, none of my friends ever called me the “Fattest Man In Piedmont”…
or at least not to me fat face. 🤣

After all the controversy with @jettson18 waving @kenroczen94 by during Moto 2 of the Chicago @supermotocross and recently receiving a written warning from the AMA, I want to set the record straight. 
I did not, I repeat DID NOT wave @carsonbrown_910 by in the second Moto of the @vurbmoto “Fastest Man In Piedmont” title showdown! 
Though I narrowly beat him in Moto 1, I couldn’t match Carson’s speed in Moto 2 and he beat me straight up with 2-1 scores. 
Sure, he won the race but thanks to the @ama_racing rule 2.2.2. which clearly states that the rider must reside in Piedmont, SC 29673 in order to be eligible for the title, I was able to retain the FMIP crown! 👑

If you’re going to Aruba, please book a tour with Sandra and Jhonatan of @epictrailAruba and tell’em Karl sent ya! 

And oh yeah, Happy 50th Birthday Cristina and Thank You for letting us celebrate YOU with your family! ❤️🙏

In 2019, we dropped off a kid at Clemson and watched him walk into his dorm. Last night, we watched a man walk across the stage to receive his Bachelor of Science in Computer Science from @clemsonuniversity 👨🏾‍🎓💻

While I’m incredibly proud of Craten’s academic accomplishments, I’m even more proud of the person he is. His morals, values and character are something I admire and they will continue to make him a great man. 

I’m so thankful God created Craten and I’m thankful for the choice his birth Mother made, to allow his Mom and I the Blessing of adopting him. His existence has had a huge impact on our families and we are all incredibly proud of him. 

Craten will now begin seeking opportunities to apply his education and make his own way in the world. I have faith that he will succeed in whatever path he takes and I can’t wait to watch his life journey. 

Keep being YOU buddy! ❤️
#ClemsonGraduate 
#ProudDad

The word GIFT is synonymous with Christmas, but we often times focus on the worldly meaning. In that context, the word “gift” can create anxiety and tension for many. Buying gifts, giving gives, receiving gifts we do (or don’t) like. Can we afford the gift? What if they don’t like their gift? What if they get me a gift and I don’t get them one?

Yesterday during Church, Craten said; “Dad, I going to be honest with you. I couldn’t think of anything to get you for Christmas.” 

Knowing that I’m hard to buy for as I’m Blessed to have everything I need and most of what I want, I told him; “That’s perfectly OK buddy. You being such a fine young man and coming to Church with me is the best gift you could give me” 

On this Christmas day, I ask you to focus on God’s greatest gift to us all. His son Jesus. 

John 3:16: “For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life

And also to be thankful for the unique gifts that God has given each of us. 

James 1:17: “Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow due to change.”

And I challenge us all to use those unique gifts in a manner that shares His love with those around us. 

1 Peter 4:10 Each of you should use whatever gift you have received to serve others, as faithful stewards of God’s grace in its various forms.

I hope you and your families are healthy, happy and loved this Christmas. 🙏❤️🙌

#BlessedByAdoption

With all the talk about A1 and @supercrosslive being broadcast in Spanish, here’s a flashback to a Japanese broadcast of the 1993 SX opening round in Orlando, FL. 
I’ll translate some of the key announcing moments for those who don’t speak Japanese. 😉

“Semi Race about to begin. Five riders will go to the Main Event. Notable racers are Jeff Emig, Larry Ward, multi-time Japanese National Champion Kohji Ohkawara and making his SX debut, Randy Richardson aka the Fastest Man In Piedmont”

“The 30 second card goes sideways”

“It’s Emig with the holeshot with Randy Richardson coming in HOT on the outside!” 

“Larry Ward continues to pressure Factory Yamaha’s Jeff Emig”

“Kohji Ohkawara on the number 311 makes a kamikaze pass on the number 222 Richardson for 5th place”

“Jeff Emig with the win followed by Suzuki’s Larry Ward, Vince DeVane, Canada’s Bill Wallin and Kohji Ohkawara in 5th” 

In case you’re wondering….
Yes; I finished 6th, missing making the 250cc Main Event in my first ever SX

Yes; 31 years later and I’m still pissed at @jimholley10 for bringing Kohji Ohkawara to the US! 😡

@jorgeprado61 leaning on his @mxgp experience in his @supercrosslive debut at A1 reminds me of another SX rookie’s debut in Orlando…  a mere 31 years ago. 👀

Jorge 📸 by @trevornelsonofficial
